index.DIV_2: Broadway & Chipping Campden stores opening soon!
index.DIV_3: Interior lifestyle that evokes vintage luxury
index.DIV_4: We have created a new concept for an interior lifestyle that embraces some important values, looking back at a time when life was a little slower and there was just…. more time, less rushing. Slowing the pace, being with friends and family in a home that is an eclectic mix of beautiful things entwined with luxurious fabrics, is a way to gain more peace of mind. Our collection of designs, antique finds and carefully curated products, is all about being immersed in something a little old fashioned but realised with a modern twist, designed to create that home from home feeling that makes you want to just sit down, read a book, write a letter and feel content, unhurried. It’s all luxuriously simple.

about.H1_55: Moving to the beautiful and historic Cotswold town Chipping Campden proved a turning point in a busy and eclectic career for illustrator Sam Wilson
about.P_56: Chipping Campden is steeped in the Arts & Crafts movement, a heritage that surrounds the British countryside. From her first tea towel design that sold like hot cakes, Sam fell in love with printing on fabric, which grew in to a business and a passion for bringing the countryside in to the home. That was 2015. Now with three Sam Wilson shops and stocked in shops and galleries all over the British Isles, Sam has a distinctive illustrative style that her customers have come to recognise, love and collect. She has even caught the eye of HRH the Prince of Wales, with two commissions from the Prince’s Regeneration Trust to her name already.
about.H1_57: Inspired by the flora and fauna of the British countryside Sam has created a collection of luxury homeware that has a natural charm
about.P_58: From her Cotswold base Sam takes her sketchbooks and camera out on long country walks observing the seasons that become the inspiration for her fabrics and products. Many are created in her studio as lino prints, a traditional printmaking craft, or in mixed media original art. Tradition and craft lie at the heart of Sam’s design ethos and that includes working and supporting a great British manufacturing heritage – textiles from Lancashire, ceramics from Stoke on Trent.
about.H1_61: “Life takes you on lots of paths and I’m so pleased I have trodden this one. I feel very proud.” Sam x

our-stores.P_66: The first Sam Wilson shop opened here in 2016. The building housed the post office from 1967 and has been an important retail building in the town for well over 150 years. It’s a fitting part of its history this shop isa new emporium for traditional craft and design in the heart of Arts & Crafts territory.
our-stores.P_82: Opened in 2018 this is Sam’s second shop. Stow is the highest of the Cotswold towns and marks the point where six roads meet including the Roman Fosse Way. It is steeped in history mainly for major sheep markets held in The Square and the part the town played in the last battle of the English Civil War.
our-stores.P_98: Sam Wilson’s third shop opened in 2019 in the heart of this historic city. Milsom Street is the most prestigious and famous of Bath’s shopping areas. The beautiful buildings were originally built as grand town houses in 1762 and mentioned in several of Jane Austen’s novels including Persuasion and Northanger Abbey. No 36 is a Grade 2 listed building with a distinctive Bath stone façade.

delivery.P_5: Free standard delivery is applied to all UK orders with a value over £50 (UK Mainland, Northern Ireland, Channel Islands & Isle of Man only). Orders under £50 will be subject to a flat rate shipping charge of £2.95.
delivery.P_8: Free standard delivery is applied to all EU orders (excluding UK) with a value over £75. Orders under £75 will be subject to a flat rate shipping charge of £9.95.
delivery.STRONG_10: USA, Canada, Rest of the World
delivery.P_12: Free standard delivery is applied to all North America and Rest of the World orders with a value over £150. Orders under £150 will be subject to a flat rate shipping charge of £19.95***.*** Prices based on orders weighing up to 1 kilogram and price may be adjusted based on size of shipping box. We will get in touch with you if extra shipping costs will be made to your order before shipment.
delivery.EM_13: (The above shipping prices are inclusive of VAT where applicable.)
delivery.P_17: For smaller orders of our smaller items please email us and we can sometimes reduce the shipping costs for overseas customers. For example we can supply cushions without the fillers which are then much more reasonable to ship worldwide.  Non-fragile goods such as tea towels or fabrics are often easier too, and unframed prints can be supplied rolled instead of flat. Please get in touch and we'll see what we can do.
delivery.P_21: Orders are generally dispatched by DPD. We endeavor to dispatch orders within 2 days of receipt. Please be aware during busy periods orders may take longer to dispatch.
delivery.P_25: Once your order has been dispatched our couriers will notify you of a delivery time by email and/or by text.

returns.P_4: We hope that you love your purchase, but understand that sometimes things just aren't quite right. If you decide something isn’t for you, simply return it to us in the same condition it was received and we’ll refund the cost of the item – no questions asked. Our returns policy means you have 30 days from receipt of the product to let us know you want to return an item, subject to the exclusions outlined below.
returns.STRONG_5: I would like to return my product, what do I need to do?
returns.P_7: To return your product/s, please follow these simple steps;
returns.P_8: Email us your return request at
returns.P_11: Send your product back to the address details we provide you, within 14 days of notifying us of your intention to return. We recommend you send your product by recorded delivery, and retain proof of postage just in case anything goes missing.
returns.P_12: Ensure returned products are sent and received in their original packaging and in a re-sellable condition.
returns.P_13: For customers returning goods from outside of the EU and/or needing to produce a customs declaration,

returns.P_17: The below are non-cancellable and non-refundable:
returns.P_18: Any product that has been used, returned without original packaging or tags or is returned in an unsaleable condition. Faulty items must be returned in their original packaging.
returns.P_19: Gift vouchers, fabric by the metre, made-to-measure and bespoke pieces.
returns.P_21: Damaged items not notified to us within 30 days of receipt.
returns.STRONG_22: Can I return a product for an exchange instead of a refund?
returns.P_23: If you wish to exchange a product, please return your item by following the standard returns procedure and contacting our team via email on office@samwilsonstudio.com to confirm your exchange request.
returns.P_27: If you would like to know exactly when your return is received by us we would advise sending your returns by a tracked service.
returns.P_29: Smaller goods can also be returned to any of our stores
returns.P_30: We ask that you return products to us unused, in their original packaging.
returns.P_31: Please bring a proof of purchase with you (i.e. store receipt, gift receipt or email order confirmation).
returns.P_32: Any returned goods must be returned to us within 30 days of delivery (online/mail order) or purchase (in-store) for a refund.
returns.P_34: If your product is damaged, faulty, or you have received an incorrect product, we will refund the cost of return shipping if you are asked to return it back to us. However, this must be reported to us and our team will assist from there. Faulty items must be returned in their original packaging.
returns.P_35: If you are returning a product for any other reason (e.g. it is different to expected or not suitable), we are unable to cover the cost of return.
returns.STRONG_36: When will my refund come through?
returns.P_37: Our team will always get in touch when a refund is due or has been requested. Once we have confirmed the refund has been processed please allow 3-5 working days for the funds to be received back into your payment account.

shop-home.P_80: Moving to the beautiful and historic Cotswold town Chipping Campden proved a turning point in a busy and eclectic career for illustrator Sam Wilson. Chipping Campden is steeped in the Arts & Crafts movement, a heritage that surrounds the British countryside.
shop-home.P_81: From her first tea towel design that sold like hot cakes, Sam fell in love with printing on fabric, which grew in to a business and a passion for bringing the countryside in to the home. That was 2015. Now with three Sam Wilson shops and stocked in shops and galleries all over the British Isles, Sam has a distinctive illustrative (painterly?)style that her customers have come to recognise, love and collect.

shop-home.P_89: Sam’s inspiration for her shop interiors harks back to the romance of an old fashioned general store = beautiful buildings, bare floor boards, stone walls, bags of character and a personal service. Her constant hunt for vintage pieces, originally intended to display her own homewares, are now part of the whole look and for sale. Sam’s shops are constantly evolving, constantly changing and a place for customers to linger and enjoy. Things move just a little bit more gently in a Sam Wilson shop
